async app.dependencies.auth.check_is_admin(user: User = Depends(get_current_user)) → User¶

The check_is_admin function is a dependency that can be used to check if the user has admin privileges. It will raise an HTTPException with status code 403 (Forbidden) if the user does not have admin privileges.

Parameters:

user – User: Get the user from the database

Returns:

The user object if the role is admin and the user is active

Doc-author:

Trelent

async app.dependencies.auth.check_is_default_user(user: User = Depends(get_current_user)) → User¶

The check_is_default_user function is a dependency that can be used to check if the user has the role of USER, MANAGER or ADMIN. It also checks if the user is active. If both conditions are met, it returns the current user object.

Parameters:

user – User: Get the user object from the database

Returns:

A user object if the role is user, manager or admin and if the user is active

Doc-author:

Trelent

async app.dependencies.auth.check_is_manager(user: User = Depends(get_current_user)) → User¶

The check_is_manager function is a dependency that checks if the user has the role of manager or admin. If they do, then it returns their User object. If not, it raises an HTTPException with status code 403.

Parameters:

user – User: Pass the user object to the function

Returns:

A user object if the user is a manager or admin and has an active account

Doc-author:

Trelent

app.dependencies.auth.create_access_token(username: str, role: str)¶
The create_access_token function creates a JWT token for the user.
The token is created with the following data:

  • sub (subject): username of the user, which is used to identify them in our database.

  • role: role of the user, which determines what they can do on our website.

  • exp (expiration time): expiration time of 1 day from now.

Parameters:

  • username – str: Specify the username of the user that is logging in

  • role – str: Specify the role of the user

Returns:

A token

Doc-author:

Trelent

app.dependencies.auth.decode_jwt_token(token)¶

The decode_jwt_token function takes a token as an argument and decodes it using the jwt.decode function. The decode_jwt_token function returns the decoded payload.

Parameters:

token – Decode the token

Returns:

The decoded payload from the token

Doc-author:

Trelent

async app.dependencies.auth.get_current_user(token: str = Depends(OAuth2PasswordBearer), db: sessionmaker(class_='Session', bind=Engine(sqlite:///./demo.db), autoflush=False, autocommit=False, expire_on_commit=True) = Depends(get_db))¶

The get_current_user function is a dependency that can be injected into any endpoint. It will decode the JWT token and return the user object if it exists.

Parameters:

  • token – str: Get the token from the request header

  • db – SessionLocal: Pass the database session to the function

Returns:

The user object

Doc-author:

Trelent
